FBIS4-24434 "drchi104_p_94007" FBIS-CHI-94-104 Daily Report 24 May 1994 Central-South Region Hainan Secretary Meets Hong Kong Trade Group Hainan Secretary Meets Hong Kong Trade Group HK2605120294 Haikou Hainan People's Radio Network in Mandarin 2300 GMT 24 May 94 HK2605120294 Haikou Hainan People's Radio Network Mandarin BFN [Text] Yesterday afternoon, Ruan Chongwu, provincial party committee secretary and governor, met in China Hainan Reform and Development Research Institute with a 12-member Hong Kong Trade Development Council [TDC] delegation headed by Francis Lo, Hong Kong TDC executive director, and Mary Wong, Hong Kong TDC assistant executive director. During the meeting, Ruan Chongwu briefed the Hong Kong guests on Hainan's investment environment, preferential taxation policies, and convenient and efficient enterprise registration process. The Hong Kong TDC delegation expressed profound interest in Hainan's development prospects. Over the next few days, the Hong Kong TDC delegation will hold separate talks with Hainan's economic cooperation, commercial and trade, and financial and banking departments on a number of cooperation projects. Persons in charge of the provincial economic cooperation department, commercial and trade department, foreign affairs office, and other departments concerned were also present during the meeting.
